title: Shana B - Leters to My Yung Gunnaz
description:
TITLE OF TAPE: Letters To My Yung Gunnaz
Artist: Shana B 
Label: Serious Business Ent.

Blurb 
I rap about what I know and even though I'm still a child technically I understand that I am also an endangered species I have buried more of my friends in my short life than my parents have in their entire life!!! Enjoy my truth......Love Shana B. Thank God for my many blessings!!!

Bio:

Born July 21, 1998 as Rashana Buchannon, I was born and raised in the city of Saint Louis, MO. We first 

lived in downtown Saint Louis, then to the West side of Saint Louis, MO.   Scheduled to graduate May 

13, 2016 alongside of my twin brother Rashad whom we call Ra-Ra. I have always been a very out spoken 

person, who has always enjoyed music. One day I was just free styling to a beat and I recorded it, so 

my big sister Courtnei asked my mother, mama have you heard Shana's song and mama said no so she played 

it for my mama and it's been work ever since, my mama played it for my dad, then he played it for his 

friends and I have been doing this thing every day!!  I sing about what I know and even though I'm 

still a child technically I understand that I am also an endangered species I have buried more of my 

friends in my short life than my parents have in their entire life!!! Enjoy my truth......Love Shana B. 

Thank God for my many blessings!!! Thank My Parent's (Dion & Coby) for believing in me and having my 

back through WHATEVA!!! LOL Thank my siblings Courtnei and Ra Ra, for the disagreements that push me 

harder to be a better me!!R.I.P. (FAT MAN, KURRON, DRAMA, BOOSIE) FLY HIGH MY BROS. I'M ABOUT TO PUT 

SUMN DOWN FOR Y'ALL!!
